{"cursor":"1432","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nIn quantum mechanics, and especially quantum information theory, the 'purity' of\na quantum state is a scalar defined as\n\n: \\gamma \\, \\equiv \\, \\mbox{Tr}(\\rho^2) \\,\n\nwhere \\rho \\, is the density matrix of the state. The purity can\nrange between unity, corresponding to a completely pure state, and 1/d\n\\, , corresponding to a completely mixed state. (Here, d \\,\nis the dimension of the density matrix.)\n\nPurity is trivially related to the Linear entropy S_L \\, of\na state by\n: \\gamma = 1-S_L \\, .\n","linknr":105,"url":"Purity_(quantum_mechanics)","recorded":1362890420,"links":16,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Quantum mechanics"],"headings":["Projectivity of a measurement","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/a/b/aab086434375635f2e3aee14dfeb575e.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/a/b/4/ab4c699d5daae16f90abf620d960811a.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/4/a/74a8d487f2b3f796a5022e6d53175d78.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/d/6/3d6de401d007ea0cffc99610ad623239.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/5/2/0524ee9a5376a290d5d3fca5c2aa82f4.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/c/3/0c3721924f697e6357852f312020a190.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Hydrogen300.png/30px-Hydrogen300.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Quantum_mechanics","Quantum_information","Density_matrix","Dimension","Linear_entropy","Quantum_tomography","Quantum_tomography","Quantum_Retrodiction"]}